reviewText: I love this DVD, my wife and I haven't laughed so hard in a while.
I loved it BUT I remember it as a kid and I also got to meet Edgar Bergan in person when he visited our ranch.  It is very old humor and probably would not be for younger generations

If you grew up listening to these guys on the radio like I did then you will enjoy revisiting those "radio days" - I listened to The Lone Ranger, The Shadow (knows what evil lurks in the minds of men), and Jack Benny, and Edger Bergen & Charlie McCarthy
Nostalgic fun.  Really takes you back in time to a different era.
The Collection DVD is a must have ...
Kind of weak, great to see rare stuff by these guys but it just left me flat.
The only issue is the watermark on the top right corner.
Great Christmas gift for my father who loves Old Time Radio programs.
Great Ventriloquist who opened the door for Jim Henson to make it on television.
